resentatives%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhern.house.gov%2Fuploadedfiles%2Ffinal_budget_including_letter_web_version.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereleased%20its%202025%20fiscal%20year%20budget%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20week.%20The%20budget%20is%20unlikely%20to%20pass%20any%20time%20soon%20but%20offers%20a%20glimpse%20of%20Republican%20priorities%20should%20they%20win%20in%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20budget%20aims%20to%20reform%20school%20lunch%20subsidies%20by%20eliminating%20the%20%26quot%3Bcommunity%20eligibility%20provision%26quot%3B%20from%20the%20federal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fns.usda.gov%2Fnslp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESchool%20Lunch%20Program%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20community%20eligibility%20provision%20funds%20school%20lunches%20for%20all%20children%20enrolled%20in%20the%20school%20regardless%20of%20their%20individual%20needs.%20The%20proposed%20RSC%20Budget%20would%20eliminate%20that%20provision%20to%20ensure%20school%20lunch%20provisions%20go%20to%20only%20%26quot%3Btruly%20needy%20households%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20only%20nine%20states%20that%20provide%20free%20school%20lunch%20to%20all%20students%20regardless%20of%20their%20status%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nycfoodpolicy.org%2Fstates-that-have-passed-universal-free-school-meals%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENYC%20Food%20Policy%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Hunter%20College.%20States%20with%20universal%20free%20lunch%20include%20California%2C%20Colorado%2C%20Illinois%2C%20Michigan%2C%20Minnesota%2C%20Main%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmassachusetts-millionaire-tax-gets-kids-free-school-lunches-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMassachusetts%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20New%20Mexico%2C%20and%20Vermont.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilar%20bills%20have%20also%20been%20considered%20by%20lawmakers%20in%20more%20than%2020%20states%20and%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERep.%20Kevin%20Hern%20of%20Oklahoma%2C%20chair%20of%20the%20RSC%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20the%20budget%20addresses%20growing%20federal%20debts%20and%20is%20%26quot%3Bproof%20that%20it's%20possible%20to%20balance%20the%20budget%2C%20it's%20possible%20to%20operate%20in%20the%20black.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConservative%20policies%20work%20together%20across%20the%20whole%20of%20government%20to%20lower%20spending%2C%20lower%20taxes%2C%20decrease%20the%20size%20and%20scope%20of%20the%20federal%20government%2C%20and%20spur%20economic%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20Hern%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frsc-hern.house.gov%2Fmedia%2Fpress-releases%2Frsc-releases-fy25-budget-proposal-fiscal-sanity-save-america%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20RSC%20budget%20says%20that%20it%20would%20give%20states%20block%20grants%20for%20child%20nutrition%20programs%20that%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Bphased-in%20state%20cost%20share%26quot%3B%20to%20incentivize%20efficient%20distribution%20and%20prevent%20what%20it%20calls%20%26quot%3Bwidespread%20fraud%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECrystal%20FitzSimons%2C%20director%20of%20child%20nutrition%20programs%20and%20policy%20at%20the%20Food%20Research%20%26amp%3B%20Action%20Center%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheintercept.com%2F2024%2F03%2F21%2Fhouse-republicans-ban-universal-school-lunches%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Intercept%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20this%20kind%20of%20proposal%20has%20been%20floated%20before%20but%20couldn't%20gain%20traction%20because%20it%20threatens%20crucial%20standards%20for%20nutrition%20in%20schools.%20It%20also%20creates%20onerous%20administrative%20work%20for%20schools%20and%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20this%20point%2C%20we%20have%20over%2040%2C000%20schools%20participating%20in%20community%20eligibility%2C%20and%20that%20allows%20them%20to%20offer%20breakfast%20and%20lunch%20to%20all%20students%20at%20no%20charge%2C%26quot%3B%20FitzSimons%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouse-republican-budget-universal-free-school-lunch-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711313239000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6600894a16bde8d4ead19687%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouse-republican-budget-universal-free-school-lunch-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Only%20nine%20states%20offer%20universal%20free%20school%20lunch.%20A%20Republican%20congressional%20caucus%20wants%20to%20make%20free%20school%20lunch%20need%20based.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kniemeyer%40insider.com%20(Kenneth%20Niemeyer)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A81%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouse-republican-budget-universal-free-school-lunch-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Citigroup%20division%20beset%20by%20sexual-harassment%20claims%20was%20also%20the%20worst%20performer%20among%20big%20banks%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22citi%20citigroup%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5359903f69bedd774ec3d58a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222411%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20culture%20of%20harassment%20and%20discrimination%20reportedly%20plagues%20Citigroup's%20equities-trading%20division.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FBrendan%20McDermid%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBloomberg%20reported%20new%20details%20about%20sexual%20harassment%20in%20Citigroup's%20equities%20division.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20former%20managing%20director%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20last%20year%2C%20saying%20the%20toxic%20culture%20persisted%20until%202022.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDuring%20that%20time%2C