er%20Kermit%20the%20Frog.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20new%20discovery%20should%20help%20scientists%20understand%20how%20these%20ancient%20species%20evolved.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20say%20they%20have%20discovered%20a%20new%20species%20of%20proto-amphibian%20that%20lived%20270%20million%20years%20ago%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they've%20named%20it%20after%20%26quot%3BThe%20Muppets%20Show%26quot%3B%20character%20Kermit%20the%20Frog.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaleontologists%20at%20the%20Smithsonian%20National%20Museum%20of%20Natural%20History%20found%20the%20ancient%20amphibian%20ancestor's%20fossilized%20skull%20while%20searching%20through%20the%20museum's%20archives%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.si.edu%2Fnewsdesk%2Freleases%2Fresearchers-name-prehistoric-amphibian-ancestor-discovered-smithsonian-collection%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estatement%20released%20by%20the%20museum.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20skull%2C%20which%20measures%20around%20an%20inch%20long%20and%20has%20%26quot%3Boval-shaped%20eye%20sockets%2C%26quot%3B%20was%20first%20discovered%20by%20Nicholas%20Hotton%20III%2C%20a%20paleontologist%20and%20curator%20at%20the%20Smithsonian%2C%20in%201984.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20unearthed%20the%20skull%20while%20exploring%20the%20Red%20Beds%2C%20a%20fossil-rich%20rock%20outcrop%20in%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20that%20season%2C%20Hotton%20discovered%20so%20many%20fossils%20that%20%26quot%3Bthey%20were%20not%20able%20to%20study%20them%20all%20in%20detail%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fossil%20then%20spent%20nearly%20the%20next%2040%20years%20sitting%20in%20the%20museum's%20archives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%202021%2C%20Arjan%20Mann%2C%20a%20postdoctoral%20paleontologist%20at%20the%20museum%20and%20a%20coauthor%20of%20the%20study%2C%20came%20across%20the%20skull%20while%20looking%20through%20Hotton's%20collection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20fossil%20immediately%20jumped%20out%20at%20me%20%E2%80%94%20this%20really%20well%20preserved%2C%20mostly%20prepared%20skull%2C%26quot%3B%20Mann%20said%20in%20the%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20determined%20that%20the%20fossil%20was%20a%20temnospondyl%2C%20a%20type%20of%20amphibian%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jurassiccoast.org%2Fscience-and-heritage%2Fpalaeontology%2Fpalaeoecology%2Ftemnospondyl%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresembled%20a%20giant%20toad%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20had%20unique%20features%20%E2%80%94%20the%20part%20of%20the%20skull%20where%20the%20animal's%20eye%20sockets%20were%20%26quot%3Bmuch%20shorter%20than%20its%20elongated%20snout%2C%26quot%3B%20leading%20them%20believe%20it%20was%20a%20new%20genus%20%E2%80%94%20Kermitops%20gratus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20think%20that%20the%20animal%20likely%20%26quot%3Bresembled%20a%20stout%20salamander.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20findings%20are%20detailed%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fzoolinnean%2Fadvance-article%2Fdoi%2F10.1093%2Fzoolinnean%2Fzlae012%2F7630141%3Flogin%3Dfalse%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20Wednesday%20in%20the%20Zoological%20Journal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lead%20author%20of%20the%20study%2C%20Calvin%20So%2C%20a%20doctoral%20student%20at%20George%20Washington%20University%2C%20said%20in%20the%20statement%3A%20%26quot%3BUsing%20the%20name%20Kermit%20has%20significant%20implications%20for%20how%20we%20can%20bridge%20the%20science%20that%20is%20done%20by%20paleontologists%20in%20museums%20to%20the%20general%20public.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20this%20animal%20is%20a%20distant%20relative%20of%20today's%20amphibians%2C%20and%20Kermit%20is%20a%20modern-day%20amphibian%20icon%2C%20it%20was%20the%20perfect%20name%20for%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BKermitops%20offers%20us%20clues%20to%20bridge%20this%20huge%20fossil%20gap%20and%20start%20to%20see%20how%20frogs%20and%20salamanders%20developed%20these%20really%20specialized%20traits%2C%26quot%3B%20So%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscientists-discover-new-species-name-after-kermit-frog-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711304235000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660046871caec1275a68cffb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscientists-discover-new-species-name-after-kermit-frog-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Scientists%20think%20that%20the%20animal%2C%20which%20lived%20270%20million%20years%20ago%2C%20likely%20%26quot%3Bresembled%20a%20stout%20salamander.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cmanley%40businessinsider.com%20(Cameron%20Manley)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A96%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscientists-discover-new-species-name-after-kermit-frog-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Naveen%20Jindal%2C%20Sita%20Soren%20Among%20BJP's%20Newest%20Members%20Who%20Got%20Tickets%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMr%20Jindal%20was%20also%20a%20Congress%20MP.%20He%20represented%20Kurukshetra%20constituency%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20from%202004%20to%202014%20as%20a%20Congress%20MP.%20This%20time%2C%20he%20said%20he%20wants%20to%20contribute%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi's%20agenda%20of%20'Viksit%20Bharat'.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMr%20Jindal%20had%20lost%20from%20Kurukshetra%20in%202014.%20He%20said%20the%20country%20has%20progressed%20under%20PM%20Modi's%20leadership%20in%20the%20past%2010%20years%2C%20and%20many%20historic%20steps%20such%20as%20the%20scrapping%20of%20Article%20370%20under%20the%20Constitution%20have%20been%20taken.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20dream%20of%20having%20a%20Ram%20temple%20in%20Ayodhya%20has%20also%20been%20realised%2C%20Mr%20Jin