%20attention%20on%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20claimed%20the%20perpetrators%20%26quot%3Btried%20to%20escape%20and%20were%20moving%20toward%20Ukraine%2C%20where%2C%20according%20to%20preliminary%20information%2C%20a%20window%20was%20prepared%20for%20them%20from%20the%20Ukrainian%20side%20to%20cross%20the%20state%20border.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKyiv%20rebuked%20the%20claims%20that%20the%20gunmen%20had%20links%20to%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMoscow%20was%20a%20'convenience'%20target%20for%20ISIS-K%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225300%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Moscow%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6584fa45a79e5746976c8d64%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223533%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Wednesday%20party%20took%20place%20in%20Moscow.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESecurity%20analysts%20say%20Russia's%20security%20agencies%20dropped%20the%20ball%20when%20it%20came%20to%20ISIS-K%20because%20all%20their%20energy%20is%20focused%20on%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EVera%20Mironova%2C%20an%20associate%20fellow%20at%20the%20Davis%20Center%20at%20Harvard%20University%20who%20studies%20Islamist%20terrorist%20movements%20in%20the%20former%20Soviet%20Union%2C%20told%20The%20Financial%20Times%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.ph%2F9tw2s%23selection-2309.0-2309.244%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIsis-K%20hit%20Moscow%20because%20the%20risk%20of%20capture%20was%20less.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20about%20the%20convenience%20of%20the%20target%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndeed%2C%20the%20militants%20had%20been%20planning%20to%20hit%20high-profile%20targets%20in%20Europe%20and%20develop%20their%20nihilistic%20presence%20beyond%20southwest%20Asia%20in%20December%20but%20were%20thwarted%20by%20Western%20security%20services.%