w%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Assam%20chief%20minister%20Hemant%20Biswa%20Sarma%20on%20Saturday%20(March%2023)%20said%20that%20Bengali-speaking%20Muslim%20migrants%20from%20Bangladesh%20%E2%80%9Cshould%20stop%20having%20more%20than%20two%20children%E2%80%9D%20and%20practice%20monogamy%20if%20they%20want%20to%20be%20recognised%20as%20indigenous%20to%20the%20state.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20questioning%20how%20the%20Bengali-speaking%20Muslims%20could%20claim%20to%20be%20indigenous%20if%20they%20encroached%20on%20%E2%80%98satras%E2%80%99%20(Vaishnavite%20monasteries)%20land%2C%20Sarma%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20they%20want%20to%20become%20indigenous%2C%20they%20cannot%20marry%20off%20their%20minor%20daughters.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CInstead%20of%20sending%20your%20children%20to%20%3Cem%3Emadrassas%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20educate%20them%20to%20become%20doctors%20and%20engineers%20if%20you%20want%20to%20be%20called%20indigenous%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sarma%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20they%20should%20also%20start%20sending%20their%20daughters%20to%20schools%20and%20give%20them%20the%20right%20over%20their%20fathers%E2%80%99%20properties%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3ETimes%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fguwahati%2Fassam-cm-himanta-biswa-sarma-lays-down-indigenous-rules-for-bdesh-origin-muslims%2Farticleshow%2F108739246.cms%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20are%20the%20differences%20between%20them%20and%20the%20indigenous%20people%20of%20the%20state.%20If%20they%20can%20give%20up%20these%20practices%20and%20imbibe%20the%20culture%20of%20Assamese%20people%2C%20at%20some%20point%20of%20time%20they%20too%20can%20become%20indigenous%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sarma%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAssam%E2%80%99s%20Muslim%20population%2C%20second%20largest%20in%20the%20country%20after%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20comes%20from%20two%20ethnicities%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0Bengali-speaking%20and%20Bangladesh-origin%20migrant%20Muslims%20and%20Assamese-speaking%20indigenous%20Muslims.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%202011%20census%2C%20Muslims%20account%20for%20over%2034%25%20of%20Assam%E2%80%99s%20total%20population%2C%20with%20the%20majority%20(63%25)%20being%20Bengali-speaking.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202022%2C%20around%2040%20lakh%20Assamese-speaking%20Muslims%20were%20recognised%20as%20%E2%80%9Cindigenous%20Assamese%20Muslims%E2%80%9D%20and%20a%20sub-group%20of%20the%20greater%20native%20Assamese%20community.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20cabinet-approved%20%E2%80%98indigenous%E2%80%99%20Assamese%20Muslims%2C%20who%20do%20not%20have%20any%20history%20of%20migration%20from%20Bangladesh%2C%20comprise%20five%20groups%20%E2%80%93%20Goria%2C%20Moria%2C%20Jolah%20(only%20the%20ones%20living%20in%20tea%20gardens)%2C%20Desi%20and%20Syed%20(only%20the%20Assamese-speaking).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711267136000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F23221556%2F2022_11img23_Nov_2022_PTI11_23_2022_000240B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fstop-having-multiple-children-practice-monogamy-assam-chief-minsters-rules-for-muslim-migrants%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'If%20they%20can%20give%20up%20these%20practices%20and%20imbibe%20the%20culture%20of%20Assamese%20people%2C%20at%20some%20point%20of%20time%20they%20too%20can%20become%20indigenous%2C%26quot%3B%20Hemant%20Biswa%20Sarma%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fstop-having-multiple-children-practice-monogamy-assam-chief-minsters-rules-for-muslim-migrants%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Over%2010%2C000%20Teachers%20and%2026%20Lakh%20Students%20Left%20in%20Lurch%20With%20UP%20Madrasa%20Act%20Struck%20Down%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F24122058%2F5384079694_f070e9e3f9_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20has%20declared%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Madrasa%20Act%2C%202004%20%E2%80%93%20through%20which%20madrasas%20are%20governed%20in%20the%20state%20%E2%80%93%20as%20unconstitutional%2C%20ruling%20that%20it%20violates%20the%20principle%20of%20secularism.%20The%20possibility%20of%20madrasas%20closing%20down%20following%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20has%20left%20around%2010%2C000%20madrasa%20teachers%20and%20over%2026%20lakh%20madrasa%20students%20with%20an%20uncertain%20future%2C%20said%20those%20affected%20by%20the%20verdict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20directed%20the%20Adityanath-led%20state%20government%20to%20take%20%E2%80%9Csteps%20forthwith%E2%80%9D%20for%20accommodating%20the%20large%20number%20of%20madrasa%20students%20in%20regular%20state-run%20schools%20at%20the%20primary%2C%20secondary%20and%20intermediate%20levels.%20Sufficient%20number%20of%20additional%20seats%20must%20be%20created%20and%20if%20required%2C%20sufficient%20number%20of%20new%20schools%20should%20also%20be%20established%20to%20accommodate%20these%20students%2C%20Justices%20Vivek%20Chaudhary%20and%20Subhash%20Vidyarthi%20directed%20the%20Adityanath%20government%20in%20a%20judgment%20dated%20March%2022.%20Madrasa%20associations%20said%20they%20would%20challenge%20the%20HC%20decision%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20even%20as%20they%20wondered%20what%20would%20be%20the%20immediate%20impact%20of%20the%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%2016%2C513%20recognised%20madrasas%2C%20out%20of%20which%20560%20are%20aided%20by%20the%20government%2C%20and%20over%208%2C400%20unrecognised%20madrasas%20in%20UP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIftikhar%20Ahmed%20Javed%2C%20chairman%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Board%20of%20Madrasa%20Education%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20HC%E2%80%99s%20decision%20would%20impact%20over%2026%20lakh%20students%20%E2%80%93%2019.5%20lakh%20in%20recognised%20madrasas%20and%20seven%20lakh%20in%20unrecognised%20madrasas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Secularism%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20division%20bench%20of%20the%20HC%2C%20while%20ruling%20the%20Act%20as%20unconstitutional%2C%20said%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdenial%E2%80%9D%20of%20modern%20education%20and%20quality%20of%20education%20in%20madrasas%20violated%20constitutional%20norms%20mandating%20free%20and%20compulsory%20education%20of%20all%20children%20in%20the%20age%20group%20of%20six%20to%2014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20the%20students%20of%20all%20other%20religions%20are%20getting%20educated%20in%20all%20modern%20subject%20denial%20of%20the%20same%20quality%20by%20the%20Madrasa%20Board%20amounts%20to%20violation%20of%20both%20Article%2021-A%20as%20well%20as%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%20The%20State%20cannot%20hide%20behind%20the%20lame%20excuse%20that%20it%20is%20fulfilling%20its%20duty%20by%20providing%20traditional%20education%20on%20nominal%20fee%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20HC%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20HC%20passed%20the%20judgment%20on%20a%20petition%20filed%20by%20a%20lawyer%2C%20Anshuman%20Singh%20Rathore%2C%20who%20had%20submitted%20that%20the%20Madrasa%20Act%20violated%20secularism%20and%20failed%20to%20provide%20quality%20compulsory%20education%20up%20to%20the%20age%20of%2014%20years%20or%20class%208%2C%20as%20was%20mandatorily%20required%20to%20be%20provided%20under%20Article%2021-A%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20Rathore%20also%20contended%20that%20the%20Madrasa%20Act%20failed%20to%20provide%20universal%20and%20quality%20school%20education%20to%20all%20the%20children%20studying%20in%20madrasas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20HC%20in%20an%2086-page%20judgment%2C%20ruled%20that%20the%20Madrasa%20Act%20was%20%E2%80%9Cviolative%20of%20the%20principle%20of%20Secularism%2C%20which%20is%20a%20part%20of%20the%20basic%20structure%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20The%20Act%20was%20violative%20of%20Articles%2014%2C%2021%20and%2021-A%20of%20the%20Constitution%20and%20Section%2022%20of%20the%20University%20Grants%20Commission%20Act%2C%201956%2C%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bench%2C%20after%20analysing%20the%20syllabus%20of%20madrasas%20from%20class%201%20to%2012%2C%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20education%20under%20the%20Madrasa%20Act%20was%20%E2%80%9Ccertainly%20not%20equivalent%20to%20the%20education%E2%80%9D%20being%20imparted%20to%20the%20students%20of%20other%20regular%20educational%20institutions%20recognized%20by%20the%20state%20boards.%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6the%20education%20being%20imparted%20in%20Madrasas%20is%20neither%20%E2%80%98quality%E2%80%99%20nor%20%E2%80%98universal%E2%80%99%20in%20nature%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20HC%20observed%20that%20the%20syllabus%20of%20class%201%20to%208%20in%20madrasas%20%E2%80%9Cshows%20that%20the%20study%20of%20Islam%20is%20necessary%20in%20every%20class%20along%20with%20the%20study%20of%20languages%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Cstudent%20cannot%20get%20promoted%20to%20the%20next%20class%E2%80%9D%20unless%20he%20or%20she%20clears%20their%20exam%20in%20religion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQuran%20and%20Islam%2C%20amongst%20other%20subjects%2C%20are%20taught%20in%20every%20class%20from%20class%201%20to%208%2C%20the%20court%20noted.%C2%A0%20In%20class%2010%20(maulvi%20or%20munshi)%2C%20Theology%20Sunni%20and%20Theology%20Shia%20are%20compulsory%20subjects%20while%20only%20one%20optional%20subject%20was%20required%20to%20be%20taken%20from%20among%20Maths%2C%20Home%20Science%20(only%20for%20girls)%2C%20Logic%20and%20Philosophy%2C%20Social%20Science%20and%20Tib%20(medical%20science).%20In%20class%2012%20(alim)%2C%20Theology%20(both%20Sunni%20and%20Shia)%20are%20compulsory%20subjects%20while%20one%20of%20the%20optional%20subjects%20is%20to%20be%20chosen%20from%20home%20science%20(only%20girls)%2C%20Hindi%2C%20Logic%20and%20Philosophy%2C%20Tib%2C%20Social%20Science%2C%20Science%20and%20Typing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fsalaray-5-years-dues-union-government-madrasa-teachers-dire-straits%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Imagine%20Not%20Getting%20Paid%20for%205%20Years%E2%80%99%3A%20Awaiting%20Dues%20From%20Centre%2C%20Madrasa%20Teachers%20in%20Dire%20Straits%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98All%20subjects%20are%20taught%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWahidullah%20Khan%2C%20national%20general%20secretary%20of%20the%20All-India%20Teachers%20Association%2C%20Madarsa%20Arabia%2C%20said%20the%20madrasas%20were%20neither%20being%20run%20merely%20for%20transmitting%20religious%20education%20nor%20were%20they%20receiving%20grants%20for%20that%20purpose.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGrants%20are%20given%20for%20the%20promotion%20of%20the%20oriental%20languages%20(Arabic%2C%20Persian%20and%20Sanskrit)%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Khan.%20The%20only%20difference%20is%20that%20while%20the%20Vedic%20schools%20are%20run%20by%20the%20state%20education%20department%2C%20the%20madrasas%20have%20since%201996%20been%20governed%20by%20the%20minority%20department%2C%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20Arbi-Farsi%20Board%20(Arabic-Persian)%20later%20became%20the%20Madrasa%20Board.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20our%20syllabus%20we%20impart%20modern%20education.%20And%20all%20subjects%20are%20taught%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Khan%2C%20adding%20that%20even%20Hindu%20teachers%20and%20students%20teach%20and%20study%20in%20madrasas%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaved%20also%20said%20providing%20religious%20education%20was%20not%20the%20aim%20of%20madrasas%20but%20to%20keep%20languages%20alive%20and%20%E2%80%9Csave%20their%20dignity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20the%20importance%20of%20madrasas%20in%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20landscape%2C%20Javed%20said%20the%20madrasas%20were%20running%20out%20of%20places%20where%20formal%20education%20would%20take%20many%20more%20years%20to%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20places%20that%20are%20located%20in%20interior%20and%20far-off%20places%20and%20without%20schools%2C%20where%20the%20poor%20people%20send%20their%20children%20to%20madrasas%20which%20provide%20them%20free%20education%20through%20donations%20and%20zakat.%20Shutting%20them%20down%20will%20give%20rise%20to%20the%20illiteracy%20rate%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Javed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98No%20work%2C%20no%20pay%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20has%20also%20created%20a%20crisis%20for%20the%20students%20as%20well%20as%20the%20teachers%20in%20madrasas.%20Faiyaz%20Ahmed%20Misbahi%20(36)%2C%20a%20madrasa%20teacher%20in%20Balrampur%2C%20who%20has%20been%20teaching%20for%20the%20last%20nine%20years%2C%20fears%20that%20the%20HC%20verdict%20could%20render%20him%20and%20thousands%20of%20others%20without%20work.%20He%20was%20also%20concerned%20by%20the%20silence%20of%20the%20court%20on%20the%20future%20of%20teachers.%20Misbahi%20pointed%20out%20that%20while%20the%20HC%20spoke%20of%20rehabilitating%20madrasa%20students%2C%20it%20was%20quiet%20about%20the%20teachers.%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20about%20the%20teachers%3F%20They%20will%20have%20no%20work%2C%20no%20pay%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhan%20also%20raised%20similar%20questions.%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20will%20happen%20to%20the%20government%20land%20and%20the%20big%20building%20complexes%20of%20these%20madrasas%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20asked%2C%20while%20also%20asking%20how%20the%20state%20would%20execute%20the%20direction%20to%20transfer%20madrasa%20students%20to%20regular%20schools%20immediately.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMisbahi%2C%20who%20is%20also%20a%20zonal%20coordinator%20of%20the%20Teachers%20Association%20Madaris%20Arabiya%2C%20UP%20%C2%A0in%20Devipatan%20zone%2C%20said%20the%20government%20could%20have%20been%20directed%20by%20the%20court%20to%20amend%20the%20portions%20of%20the%202004%20Act%20that%20it%20deemed%20unconstitutional.%C2%A0%20He%20wondered%20how%20the%20government%20would%20accommodate%20the%20madrasa%20students%20and%20provide%20them%20quality%20education%20when%20it%20was%20already%20struggling%20to%20do%20with%20regular%20students.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20madrasas%2C%20we%20provide%20children%20free%20education%20along%20with%20food%20and%20medical%20facilities.%20Religious%20education%20is%20not%20our%20purpose.%20Since%202018%2C%20we%20have%20been%20teaching%20with%20NCERT%20Books%20and%20as%20per%20that%20syllabus%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Misbahi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20the%20Adityanath%20government%20approved%20the%20introduction%20of%20NCERT%20books%20in%20Hindi%2C%20Urdu%20and%20English%20in%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20Madrasa%20Board.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fup-government-ends-honorarium-to-madrasa-teachers-move-to-adversely-affect-1-million-students%5C%22%3EUP%20Government%20Ends%20Honorarium%20to%20Madrasa%20Teachers%2C%20Move%20to%20Adversely%20Affect%201%20Million%20Students%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Why%20so%20much%20unemployment%20then%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20associated%20with%20madrasas%20feel%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20assessment%20that%20madrasas%20lagged%20in%20providing%20quality%20and%20universal%20education%20was%20not%20accurate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20numerous%20examples%20of%20people%20who%20studied%20in%20the%20madrasa%20stream%20who%20have%20gone%20on%20to%20crack%20civil%20services%20and%20become%20IAS%20officers.%20Others%20are%20getting%20degrees%20in%20law%20and%20clearing%20medical%20entrance%20tests%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Misbahi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20madrasa-educated%20persons%20are%20also%20becoming%20professors%20at%20the%20Banaras%20Hindu%20University%2C%20Aligarh%20Muslim%20University%20and%20the%20Jamia%20Millia%20Islamia%20University%2C%20added%20Khan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAnd%20if%20we%20talk%20about%20quality%20education%20in%20a%20total%20sense%2C%20do%20all%20students%20in%20regular%20schools%20succeed%3F%20If%20they%20do%2C%20then%20why%20is%20there%20so%20much%20unemployment%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20striking%20down%20the%20Madrasa%20Act%2C%20the%20HC%20said%20that%20under%20the%20law%2C%20for%20being%20recognized%20by%20the%20Madrasa%20Board%20it%20was%20compulsory%20for%20an%20institution%20to%20be%20setup%20as%20a%20Muslim%20minority%20institution%20and%20it%20was%20also%20compulsory%20for%20a%20student%20to%20study%20in%20every%20class%2C%20Islam%20as%20a%20religion%2C%20including%20all%20its%20prescriptions%2C%20instructions%20and%20philosophies%2C%20to%20get%20promoted%20to%20next%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20HC%20also%20said%20that%20the%20State%20cannot%20%E2%80%9Cdiscriminate%20and%20provide%20different%20type%20of%20education%20to%20children%20belonging%20to%20different%20religions.%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CSuch%20an%20action%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20State%20is%20not%20only%20unconstitutional%20but%20also%20highly%20divisive%20of%20the%20society%20on%20religious%20lines.%20Any%20policy%20of%20the%20State%20which%20is%20divisive%20of%20society%20on%20religious%20lines%20is%20violative%20of%20the%20constitutional%20principles%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnion%20government%E2%80%99s%20stance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20while%20the%20Adityanath%20government%20defended%20the%20Madrasa%20Act%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20submitted%20in%20the%20court%20that%20religious%20education%20and%20religious%20instructions%20of%20a%20single%20religion%20cannot%20be%20included%20in%20school%20education%20and%20that%20the%20state%20government%20has%20no%20power%20to%20create%20statutory%20education%20boards%20permitting%20religious%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UP%20government%20and%20the%20Madrasa%20Board%20opposed%20the%20petition%20to%20declare%20the%20Act%20unconstitutional%20and%20argued%20that%20the%20State%20government%20had%20sufficient%20power%20to%20frame%20laws%20with%20regard%20to%20education%2C%20including%20traditional%20education%2C%20which%20includes%20religion.%20They%20argued%20that%20the%20State%20had%20enacted%20the%20Madrasa%20Act%20in%20exercise%20of%20its%20powers%20under%20entry%2025%20of%20list%20III%20of%20schedule%20VII%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20HC%2C%20while%20acknowledging%20the%20power%20of%20the%20state%20to%20frame%20laws%20with%20regard%20to%20education%20at%20the%20school%20level%2C%20however%2C%20stressed%20that%20such%20education%20has%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Csecular%20in%20nature.%E2%80%9D%20The%20bench%20also%20said%20that%20the%20state%20had%20no%20power%20to%20create%20a%20board%20for%20religious%20education%20or%20establish%20a%20board%20for%20school%20education%20only%20for%20a%20particular%20religion%20and%20philosophy%20associated%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20board%20and%20other%20madrasa%20associations%20also%20argued%20that%20Article%2025%20to%2029%20provided%20rights%20to%20propagate%20religion%20while%20Article%2030%20protected%20the%20rights%20of%20minorities%20to%20establish%20and%20administer%20their%20educational%20institutions.%20The%20court%2C%20however%2C%20said%20that%20Articles%2025%20to%2029%20were%20concerned%20with%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20citizens%20and%20not%20of%20the%20State.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20State%20has%20to%20remain%20secular.%20It%20must%20respect%20and%20treat%20all%20religions%20equally.%20The%20State%20cannot%2C%20in%20any%20manner%20whatsoever%2C%20discriminate%20between%20religions%20while%20performing%20its%20duties.%20It%20cannot%20provide%20for%20education%20of%20a%20particular%20religion%2C%20its%20instructions%2C%20prescriptions%20and%20philosophies%20or%20create%20separate%20education%20systems%20for%20separate%20religions%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20HC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98What%20of%20accreditation%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Madrasa%20Board%20argued%20in%20court%20that%20madrasas%20were%20providing%20%E2%80%9Cnearly%20free%20education%E2%80%9D%20to%20minor%20children%2C%20with%20a%20monthly%20fee%20of%20hardly%20Rs%2010%20or%2020%20per%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhan%20said%20his%20association%2C%20which%20had%20opposed%20the%20petition%20in%20court%2C%20will%20study%20the%20detailed%20judgment%20to%20understand%20its%20legal%20nuances.%20There%20is%20still%20some%20confusion%20on%20the%20scope%20of%20its%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20government%20wants%2C%20the%20verdict%2C%20if%20implemented%2C%20can%20impact%20all%20madrasas.%20But%20I%20think%20it%20should%20not%20impact%20any%20recognised%20madrasa%20already%20existing%20because%20the%20court%20has%20declared%20the%202004%20Act%20unconstitutional%20but%20not%20said%20if%20all%20the%20accreditation%20given%20under%20it%20would%20also%20be%20declared%20invalid%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Khan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPost-independence%2C%20private%20madrasas%20continued%20to%20run%20in%20the%20state%20but%20were%20not%20regulated%20or%20recognized%20by%20the%20government.%20It%20was%20in%201969%2C%20that%20the%20government%20for%20the%20first%20time%20came%20out%20with%20the%20%E2%80%98Rules%20of%20Recognition%20of%20Arabic%20and%20Persian%20Madarsas%2C%20U.P%2C%E2%80%99%20which%20mandated%20that%20such%20institutions%20seeking%20recognition%20apply%20to%20the%20Registrar%2C%20Arabic%20and%20Persian%20Examinations%2C%20U.P.%2C%20Allahabad.%20Then%2C%20in%201987%2C%20the%20government%20formed%20non-statutory%20rules%20for%20their%20regulation%20and%20in%201995%20created%20a%20new%20department%20called%20%E2%80%98Minority%20Welfare%20Department%E2%80%99.%20In%201996%2C%20rules%20were%20framed%20to%20transfer%20the%20working%20of%20madrasas%20and%20other%20minority-related%20schemes%20to%20the%20Minority%20Welfare%20Department%20from%20the%20state%20Education%20Department.%20The%20earlier%201987%20non-statutory%20regulations%20of%201987%20were%20replaced%20by%20the%20Madrasa%20Act%20of%202004.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711263275000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F24122058%2F5384079694_f070e9e3f9_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Futtar-pradesh-madrasa-act-allahabad-high-court%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20judgement%20declaring%20a%20key%20act%20governing%20madrasas%20illegal%20has%20left%20over%2016%2C000%20recognised%20and%20over%208%2C000%20unrecognised%20madrasas%20staring%20at%20uncertainty.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Futtar-pradesh-madrasa-act-allahabad-high-court%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Simon%20Harris%20-%20the%20man%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20Irish%20history%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711260983000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2FA86E%2Fproduction%2F_132981134_gettyimages-957575024.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-68624474%230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20favourite%20to%20replace%20Leo%20Varadkar%20as%20taoiseach%20organised%20his%20first%20political%20meeting%20aged%2016.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A55%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-68624474%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-68624474.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-68624474.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Madgaon%20Express'%3A%20The%20Boys%20Will%20Be%20Boys%20Caper%20Has%20its%20Funny%20Moments%20But%20Remains%20Conventional%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F24111342%2FScreenshot-2024-03-24-at-11.12.4.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKunal%20Kemmu%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMadgaon%20Express%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20belongs%20to%20a%20bygone%20era.%20Like%20the%20one%20that%20patronises%20young%20men%20with%20sayings%20like%20%E2%80%98boys%20will%20be%20boys%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20romanticising%20their%20ineptitude%2C%20while%20laughing%20with%20and%20at%20their%20foolhardiness.%20It%E2%80%99s%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDumb%20and%20Dumber%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E-meets-%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAndaz%20Apna%20Apna%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20flavour%20of%20comedy%20%E2%80%93%20where%20the%20male%20protagonists%20have%20questionable%20intelligence%20and%20are%20irreversibly%20on%20the%20wrong%20side%20of%20luck%2C%20so%20it%E2%80%99s%20hard%20for%20anything%20to%20go%20smoothly.%20In%20a%20film%20like%20this%2C%20a%20cup%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Echai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20will%20not%20merely%20be%20sipped%20by%20someone%2C%20like%20it%20usually%20happens%20in%20films.%20The%20cup%20will%20slip%20from%20said%20person%E2%80%99s%20hand%2C%20spill%20onto%20the%20adjacent%20person%2C%20who%20will%20accidentally%20drop%20the%20leash%20of%20their%20pet%2C%20which%20will%20run%20away%20and%20get%20electrocuted%20by%20the%20nearby%20electric%20pole.%20Or%20such%20are%20the%20gags.%20You%20get%20the%20drift%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FB7VP47oCZfE%3Fsi%3Do92IXKOs563dSqnX%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20not%20to%20say%20that%20such%20films%20are%20too%20%E2%80%98dated%E2%80%99%2C%20because%20the%20writing%20can%20hold%20a%20surprise%20every%20now%20and%20then.%20It%E2%80%99s%20something%20we%20saw%20glimpses%20of%20in%20Amar%20Kaushik%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EStree%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(2018)%20%E2%80%93%20a%20film%20that%20used%20the%20mould%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98boys%20comedy%E2%80%99%20to%20deliver%20commentary%20far%20more%20progressive%20than%20many%20of%20us%20would%20have%20expected%20from%20a%20film%20like%20that.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKunal%20Kemmu%20%E2%80%93%20who%20made%20a%20name%20for%20himself%20with%20his%20glorious%20comic-timing%20in%20films%20like%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EGo%20Goa%20Gone%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(2013)%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELootcase%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(2020)%20%E2%80%93%20makes%20his%20directorial%20debut%20here.%20The%20film%20follows%20three%20childhood%20friends%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20Dodo%20(Divyenndu)%2C%20Pinku%20(Pratik%20Gandhi)%20and%20Ayush%20(Avinash%20Tiwary)%20%E2%80%93%20desperate%20to%20make%20good%20on%20their%20plan%20for%20a%20Goa%20vacation.%20Excel%20Entertainment%20%E2%80%93%20the%20production%20house%20which%20seems%20to%20have%20patented%20the%20premise%20of%20three%20friends%20going%20on%20a%20trip%20%E2%80%94%20is%20the%20producer%20here.%20So%2C%20while%20the%20intent%20is%20to%20slight%20earlier%20films%20made%20by%20Excel%20like%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDil%20Chahta%20Hai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EZindagi%20Na%20Milegi%20Dobara%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20self-awareness%20feels%20too%20airbrushed%20and%20smug.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20laughed%20the%20loudest%20when%20the%20three%20friends%20reach%20a%20Goa%20shack%20and%20sipping%20a%20beer%20each%2C%20and%20Dodo%20asks%20the%20other%20two%3A%20%E2%80%9CEnjoy%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eho%20raha%20hai%20na%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%3F%20(we%E2%80%99re%20enjoying%2C%20right%3F)%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20A%20scene%20later%2C%20two%20of%20them%20are%20arguing%20with%20a%20jet-ski%20instructor%20about%20how%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20ride%20pillion%20because%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20how%20it%20is%20shown%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDil%20Chahta%20Hai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20It%E2%80%99s%20also%20in%20this%20very%20scene%20that%20director%20Kemmu%20makes%20a%20special%20appearance%20as%20a%20dopey%20stranger%20sitting%20at%20a%20bar%2C%20distributing%20drugs%20to%20the%20three%20friends%20by%20calling%20them%20%E2%80%98background%20music%E2%80%99%20for%20their%20Goa%20trip.%20It%E2%80%99s%20where%20the%20film%20teases%20how%20funny%20it%20could%E2%80%99ve%20been%20as%20the%20realistic%2C%20antithesis%20version%20for%20all%20the%20road%20trips%20glorified%20in%20Bollywood.%20However%2C%20things%20get%20far%20more%20conventional%20after%20this.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F24111332%2FScreenshot-2024-03-24-at-11.09.4-1024x439.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F24111332%2FScreenshot-2024-03-24-at-11.09.4-1024x439.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F24111332%2FScreenshot-2024-03-24-at-11.09.4-300x129.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F24111332%2FScreenshot-2024-03-24-at-11.09.4.png%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-703023%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22360%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20still%20from%20Madgaon%20Express.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20wild%20night%2C%20three%20childhood%20friends%2C%20a%20convenient%20switch%20of%20bags%20at%20a%20railway%20station%20which%20embroils%20them%20in%20a%20drug%20deal%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMadgaon%20Express%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99s%20plot%20isn%E2%80%99t%20nearly%20as%20crazy%20in%20a%20post-%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHangover%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20world.%20A%20lot%20of%20it%20is%20familiar%2C%20like%20someone%20accidentally%20overdosing%20on%20cocaine%2C%20eccentric%20Dons%20played%20by%20Upendra%20Limaye%20and%20Chhaya%20Kadam%20and%20the%20wisecracks%20from%20their%20respective%20gangs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20of%20the%20cast%20does%20what%20is%20expected%20of%20them%2C%20especially%20Divyenndu%20with%20his%20straight-faced%20lies%20and%20ill-timed%20rebuttals.%20But%20it%E2%80%99s%20Gandhi%20who%20walks%20away%20with%20the%20film%2C%20given%20his%20portrayal%20of%20the%20frail%20germaphobe%20Gujarati%20boy%20who%20transforms%20into%20something%20a%20Sandeep%20Reddy%20Vanga%20hero%20would%20look%20up%20to.%20I%20could%20somehow%20never%20quite%20buy%20the%20friendship%20between%20the%20three%20men%2C%20given%20how%20easy%20it%20is%20to%20pick%20apart%20Dodo%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98fake%20life%E2%80%99%20on%20Facebook.%20I%20kept%20waiting%20for%20the%20friends%20to%20come%20clean%20to%20Dodo%2C%20instead%20of%20the%20other%20way%20round.%20I%20was%20hoping%20they%20would%20tell%20him%20how%20they%20knew%20he%20was%20a%20penniless%2C%20unemployable%20man-child%2C%20but%20didn%E2%80%99t%20bring%20it%20up%20earlier%20to%20save%20him%20the%20embarrassment.%20Alas%2C%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20and%20Dodo%20gets%20an%20entire%20scene%20of%20a%20melodramatic%20confession